Executive summary
Great problem solving is hide-and-seek. Examiners hide a single clear idea — a seed — inside a deceptive wrapper designed to lure the solver into brute force or rote tricks. The real craft, whether in mathematics or physics, is to find that seed and remove the wrapper with a single elegant move.

