4. Grand Themes of Elegance (catalog & short guide)
A compact, annotated list you should master and recognize:

Symmetry & Exchangeability — swap variables, exploit equal roles.

Invariance & Monovariant — conserved quantity or monotone quantity in iterative processes.

Substitution / Change of Variables — linearizing or normalizing constraints.

Homogenization — equalizing degrees so inequalities apply.

Cauchy & Rearrangement — spotting quadratic or sum structures suggest these.

Telescoping & Cancellation — series or algebraic cancellation seeds.

Extremal Principle — smallest counterexample or maximum/minimum tactics.

Double Counting — count same set in two ways to obtain equality.

Complex/Vector Representations — geometry via algebraic objects.

Inversion — transform geometry to linear relationships.

Generating Functions / Transform Techniques — combinatoric structure recognition.

Continuity & Limit Arguments — passing to limit or approximations.

Parity & Modularity — fast elimination by residues.

Functional Equation Patterns — substitution and iteration.

(Train to map each problem to 1–3 themes quickly.)

