5.1 Examiner’s objectives
Differentiate: create tiers — easy parts to gain marks, a central twist to separate top students.

Test understanding: design wrappers that make rote formulas fail.

Reward elegance: provide an elegant pivot but hide it.

Plant traps: make brute force plausible and tempting.

