10. Curriculum & Practice Plans
10.1 Apprentice (12-month) plan — daily structure
Daily: 1 math deep commentary (90–120 min), 1 set of 6 timed short problems (60–90 min), 30 min of SRS review (one-line takeaways).

Weekly: one consolidation day — re-solve 6 commentaries from past week; peer review one commentary.

Monthly: produce a “synthesis essay” of 8–10 pivotal rules learned that month.

10.2 Advanced (18-24 month) plan
Maintain daily commentary habit but reduce to 60–90 min. Add weekly full-length mock and monthly constructed-problem exercise. Increase timed practice frequency gradually.

10.3 Metrics to monitor
#commentaries per week, seed recognition time (median), % of re-solve accuracy after 2 weeks, timed-problem accuracy rate, mock test results.

11. Assessment & Rubrics
11.1 Student commentary grading rubric (0–10)
Seed identification (2 pts): Accurate + precise.

Brute path clarity (1 pt): Described correctly; why it is tempting.

Elegant pivot (3 pts): Correctness, brevity, insight, minimal algebra.

Pitfalls & checks (1 pt): Identifies likely traps.

Connections/generalization (1.5 pts): At least two relevant links or a simple generalization.

Presentation & takeaway (1.5 pts): Clarity, concision; takeaway memorable.

Provide comments: what to improve; assign revisit date.

11.2 Problem construction grading (0–10)
Seed & elegance (3 pt), wrapper plausibility (2 pt), distractor quality (2 pt), clarity & solvability (2 pt), marking scheme (1 pt).

12. Teacher’s playbook — how to run a commentary class
12.1 Class structure (90 minutes)
Warmup (10 min): Quick seed detection drill — show 3 short problems; students write one-line seeds.

Master commentary reading (20 min): Instructor reads a master commentary aloud and annotates pivot.

Student attempt (30–35 min): Students attempt one problem in pairs and write a short commentary (seed & pivot).

Discussion & feedback (20–25 min): Two student pairs present; instructor critiques using rubric.

12.2 Peer review cycles
Assign 3 commentaries per student to review weekly. Use rubric checkboxes and 200-word feedback. Rotate reviewers monthly.

12.3 Calibration sessions
Teachers grade 10 anonymized commentaries together monthly and align scoring standards.

