Overcomplicating with algebra: Use symmetry or energy early.

Diagram sloppiness: unclear diagrams lead to sign errors; force clear labeling.

Training remedies: rubric insistence on “assumptions” box, mandatory units in final line, practice in contrastive examples where assumptions lead to different answers.

