Score: 0–2

2. Brute Path / First Impulse — 2 points
✅ Honest capture of the natural, straightforward attempt.

✅ Shows working even if it dead-ends.

❌ Skipped / over-polished (no genuine “first attempt”).
Score: 0–2

3. Elegant Pivot (Breakthrough) — 2 points
✅ Correctly identifies the key idea that simplifies the brute path.

✅ Highlights elegance, symmetry, or insight.

❌ Just a continuation of brute force without shift in thinking.
Score: 0–2

4. Pitfalls & Distractions — 1 point
✅ Explicit mention of tempting but wrong paths.

✅ Notes why they fail.

❌ Absent or superficial (“no pitfalls”).
Score: 0–1

5. Connections & Generalizations — 2 points
✅ Links to known theorems, identities, problem archetypes, or cross-theme ideas.

✅ Explores “what if” variations.

❌ Just solves problem in isolation.
Score: 0–2

6. Key Takeaway (Meta-Lesson) — 1 point
✅ One sharp, memorable insight stated clearly.

❌ Generic remark like “practice helps” or “was tough.”
Score: 0–1

7. Technical Hygiene (bonus + penalties)
+1 if LaTeX is neat, equations are properly typeset, diagrams are clear.

–1 if sloppy, unreadable, or missing key steps.

🔹 Total Score: /10
9–10 → Excellent (certification standard).

7–8 → Strong but polish needed.

5–6 → Adequate attempt, missing depth in 1–2 areas.

<5 → Needs major revision.

