Quick heuristics to pick a pivot (decision tree, ~15 seconds)
Is it symmetric/homogeneous? → try normalization or symmetric polynomials.

Is it counting/coefficient-like? → try expansion/gf.

Are operations repeated or process-driven? → look for invariants.

Are denominators/radicals present? → try substitution.

Is it a min/max? → check inequalities / extremal principles.

Is there a geometric flavor? → draw / vectorize.

Is it integer/ divisibility? → take mod, parity, LTE.

If two apply, pick the one that reduces degrees of freedom most (normalization > substitution; invariance > brute force).

