Tone: teacherly, concise, friendly. No belittling language.

Length: Stage-2 commentary ~300–800 words depending on complexity; include compact LaTeX block for core maths.

Equations: minimal, explicit, and numbered only when needed.

Diagrams: use small inline diagrams when geometry or visual pivot is crucial.

Examples: include 1–2 short cross-problems in Connections.

Metadata: complete JSON & archetype tags mandatory before final stage acceptance.

